== List of research papers for the report
Send us an email to reserve a paper and get the published version (papers which are already taken are marked as such in the list). You also have the possibility to choose a published article of your choice from the optimal transport literature, send us an email with your suggestion if you wish to do so. Report and practical sessions due on *April 7th* via an email addressed to both of us.

- 1] Korman and McCann (2012). Optimal transportation with capacity constraints.  
[http://www.math.toronto.edu/mccann/papers/OTCC.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 2] Agueh and Carlier (2010). Barycenters in the Wasserstein space. [https://www.ceremade.dauphine.fr/~carlier/AC_bary_Aug11_10.pdf pdf]  (TAKEN)
- 3] Cotar, Friesecke and Klüppelberg (2011). Density Functional Theory and Optimal Transportation with Coulomb Cost. [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1104.0603.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 4] Carlier, Duval, Peyré and Schmitzer (2017). Convergence of entropic schemes for optimal transport and gradient flows.  [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1512.02783.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 5] Buttazzo and Santambrogio (2009). A Mass Transportation Model for the Optimal Planning of an Urban Region. [http://cvgmt.sns.it/media/doc/paper/1015/sigestCVGMT.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 6] Blanchet and Carlier (2012). Optimal Transport and Cournot-Nash equilibria.  [https://www.ceremade.dauphine.fr/~carlier/blanchetcarlierfinal.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 7] Solomon, De Goes,  Peyré, Cuturi, Butscher, Nguyen and Guibas (2015). Convolutional Wasserstein distances: Efficient optimal transportation on geometric domains. [https://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/hal-01188953 pdf] (TAKEN)
- 8] Niles-Weed and Bach (2017). Sharp asymptotic and finite-sample rates of convergence of empirical measures in Wasserstein distance. [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1707.00087.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 9] Di marino and Louet (2017). The entropic regularization of the Monge problem on the real line.  [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1703.10457.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 10] Gangbo and Święch (1998). Optimal maps for the multidimensional Monge‐Kantorovich problem.  [http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.116.1489&rep=rep1&type=pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 11] Benamou, Carlier and Santambrogio (2016). Variational Mean Field Games. [http://cvgmt.sns.it/media/doc/paper/2979/BenCarSan-v4.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 12] Brenier (1991). Polar factorization and monotone rearrangement of vector‐valued functions. [https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/pdf/10.1002/cpa.3160440402?casa_token=tbJQnd7MY54AAAAA:Hjt2j5U9cEwVMNysmYAME9n7mTQMCm-Z-pVJigAk67HzFKrXxY3_KDntKS1KL2f55yFjr7BaUYKBppRO pdf] (TAKEN)
- 13] Jordan, Kinderlehrer and Otto (1998). The variational formulation of the Fokker-Planck equation. [https://www-dimat.unipv.it/savare/Ravello2010/JKO.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 14] Backhoff,  Conforti, Gentil, Léonard (2019). The mean field Schr¨odinger problem: ergodic behavior, entropy estimates and functional inequalities. [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1905.02393.pdf pdf]
- 15] Bigot, Cazelles, Papadakis (2019). Penalization of Barycenters in the Wasserstein Space. [https://www.math.u-bordeaux.fr/~jbigot/Site/Publications_files/RegBar_theory.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 16] Baradat, Monsaingeon (2019). Small noise limit and convexity for generalized
incompressible flows, Schrödinger problems, and optimal transport. [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1810.12036.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 17] McCann (1997). A Convexity Principle for Interacting Gases. [http://www.math.toronto.edu/mccann/papers/advances.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 18] Carlier, Galichon, Santambrogio (2009). From Knothe’s transport to Brenier’s map and a continuation method for optimal transport. [https://www.ceremade.dauphine.fr/~carlier/Knothe-Brenier-final.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 19] Altschuler, Weed, Rigollet (2017). Near-linear time approximation
algorithms for optimal transport via Sinkhorn iteration. [https://arxiv.org/pdf/1705.09634.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
- 20] Figalli (2009). The Optimal Partial Transport Problem. [https://web.ma.utexas.edu/users/figalli/papers/The%20optimal%20partial%20transport%20problem.pdf pdf] (TAKEN)
